Description: Linux Security Hardening Framework
 HARDN is a Linux security hardening toolkit for Debian and Ubuntu.
 It integrates essential security tools and provides a framework for
 system hardening and security compliance.
 .
 Features:
  - Automated system hardening via command-line interface
  - Real-time security monitoring and reporting
  - Comprehensive security audit and compliance checking
  - Log management and analysis tools
  - System file integrity checking
  - Intrusion detection and malware scanning
  - Integration with systemd and secure defaults
  - Command-line tools for system administration
 .
 This CLI-only version is optimized for servers, headless systems, and
 automated deployments in high-security environments.
 .
 Suitable for Debian-based servers, containers, and headless endpoints.
